		<div align="right">
		<div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a>		</div><h2 align="left"><a name="resting" id="resting"></a>Caring for Your Puffle - Resting </h2>
		<div align="right">
          <table width="100%" height="256"  border="0" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
            <tr>
              <td height="256" valign="top"><ul>
                  <li>
                    <p align="left" class="plaintext"> To let your puffle sleep, click on the second button from the left. Puffles get tired after a lot of activity and need to take naps to regain energy.</p>
                  </li> 
                  <li>
                    <p align="left" class="plaintext">Usually a puffle will need some rest after you have played with it a couple times. But be careful though, too much sleep is not good for their health.</p>
                <ul><li><div align="left"><a href="#feeding">Feeding</a></div>
                      </li>
					  <li>
                        <div align="left"><a href="#bath">Bathing</a></div>
